    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-09-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-09-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="138" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d138">
                <head>No. 14.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Earl <persName type="from">Granville</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Lowell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign
                                    Office</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-09-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 2,
                            1881</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                        yous letter of the 1st instant, urging the release from prison, on the
                        ground of ill-health, of Mr. Joseph B. Walsh, who was arrested at Castlebar,
                        in the month of March last, under the protection of persons and property
                        (Ireland) act, 1881.</p>
                <p>In reply, I beg leave to state to you that I have lost no time in referring
                        your letter to the proper department of Her Majesty’s Government, and that I
                        shall not fail to communicate further with you upon this subject.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>GRANVILLE.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
